const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Why is Sub-Zero so expensive vs other refrigerators?",
    a: "Premium engineering and lifetime construction. Dual refrigeration system (separate compressors and evaporators for fridge and freezer compartments, much more reliable than single-evaporator competitors). Lifetime stainless cabinet warranty for the original purchaser, no other brand matches this. 20 to 25+ year service life standard, vs 8 to 12 years for mid-tier brands. Per-year cost of ownership often runs lower despite higher upfront purchase price. A premium refrigerator that lasts 25 years at $14,000 works out to $560 per year. The Sub-Zero kitchen integration plus food preservation quality is in a different category from mid-tier appliances.",
