    q: "My Sub-Zero refrigerator-freezer combo has freezer cold but fridge warm. Is the whole thing failing?",
    a: "Probably not. Sub-Zero's dual refrigeration system means fridge and freezer have independent evaporator systems with separate compressors. The fridge-side condenser fan motor or evaporator can fail without affecting the freezer side. We diagnose which system has the issue and repair only that side. Most other brands use single-evaporator architecture with damper transfer, so both compartments fail together. Sub-Zero's dual-evap design is one of the reasons the brand commands its premium pricing.",
