  {
    q: "My Sub-Zero is 4 years old and uses R-600a refrigerant. Is service different?",
    a: "Yes. Newer Sub-Zero (post-2020) transitioned to R-600a hydrocarbon refrigerant for environmental compliance. Different service procedures than R-134a. R-600a is flammable, so proper handling requires specific certification beyond standard EPA 608, including different leak detection methods and separate recovery procedures. Most appliance shops don't carry R-600a training. We do.",
